{"title_page": "Edvin Murati", "text_new": "{{Expand Greek|\u0388\u03bd\u03c4\u03b2\u03b9\u03bd \u039c\u03bf\u03c5\u03c1\u03ac\u03c4\u03b9|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Edvin Murati\n| fullname = Edvin Murati\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1975|11|12}}\n| birth_place = [[Tirana]], [[Albania]]\n| height = 1.72 m\n| position = [[Midfielder]]\n| youthyears1 =\n| youthclubs1 = [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]]\n| years1 = 1994\u20131995\n| clubs1 = [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]]\n| caps1  = 0\n| goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 1995\u20131996\n| clubs2 = [[LB Ch\u00e2teauroux|Ch\u00e2teauroux]]\n| caps2  = 31\n| goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 1996\u20131997\n| clubs3 = Paris Saint-Germain\n| caps3  = 0\n| goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 1997\u20131998\n| clubs4 = [[Stade Briochin]]\n| caps4  = 1\n| goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 1998\u20131999\n| clubs5 = [[Fortuna D\u00fcsseldorf]]\n| caps5  = 11\n| goals5 = 0\n| years6 = 1999\u20132000\n| clubs6 = Paris Saint-Germain\n| caps6  = 16\n| goals6 = 0\n| years7 = 2000\u20132002\n| clubs7 = [[Lille OSC|Lille]]\n| caps7  = 29\n| goals7 = 1\n| years8 = 2002\u20132006\n| clubs8 = [[Iraklis F.C. (Thessaloniki)|Iraklis]]\n| caps8  = 66\n| goals8 = 6\n| years9 = 2007\u20132008\n| clubs9 = [[Panserraikos F.C.|Panserraikos]]\n| caps9  = 25\n| goals9 = 8\n| totalcaps = 179\n| totalgoals = 15\n| nationalyears1 = 1998\u20132006\n| nationalteam1 = [[Albania national football team|Albania]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 42\n| nationalgoals1 = 4\n}}\n'''Edvin Murati''' (born 12 November 1975) is an [[Albania]]n former professional [[Association football|footballer]]. He played for [[Panserraikos FC]] and [[Iraklis F.C.]] in Greece.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[Guardian.co.uk]]|title=Stats Centre: Edvin Murati Facts|url=http://guardian.touch-line.com/StatsCentre.asp?CTID=25&CPID=124&TEID=7457&PLID=5632&pStr=Player|accessdate=20 July 2009|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120506052536/http://guardian.touch-line.com/StatsCentre.asp?CTID=25&CPID=124&TEID=7457&PLID=5632&pStr=Player|archivedate=6 May 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> He played also in France,{{refn|{{LFP|id=murati-edvin}}}} Germany, and for the [[Albania national football team|Albanian national football team]]. In December 2018 he was honoured for his services to Albanian football, alongside [[Perlat Musta]] and [[Qamil Teliti]].<ref>[http://telegraf.al/sport/musta-murati-dhe-teliti-pas-vdekjes-dekorohen-me-nderi-i-futbollit-shqiptar/ Musta, Murati dhe Teliti (pas vdekjes) dekorohen me \u201cNderi i futbollit shqiptar\u201d] - Telegraf {{in lang|sq}}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nMurati was born in [[Tirana]]. He was coached by Luka Shaqiri. He started training with Shaqiri at age eleven. Murati was picked up by [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]].\n\n==International career==\nMurati made his debut for [[Albania national football team|Albania]] in an August 1998 [[friendly match]] away against [[Cyprus national football team|Cyprus]] and earned a total of 42 caps, scoring 4 goals.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[RSSSF]]|author=Hoxha, Florent|title=Albania \u2013 Record International Players|url=http://rsssf.com/miscellaneous/alba-recintlp.html|date=16 July 2009|accessdate=20 July 2009}}</ref> His final international was an October 2006 [[UEFA Euro 2008 qualifying|European Championship qualification]] match against the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://eu-football.info/_player.php?id=14622|title=Player Database|website=eu-football.info|accessdate=2019-09-04}}</ref> In the [[2006 FIFA World Cup qualification]], he scored a winning goal against [[UEFA Euro 2004]] Champions Team [[Greece national football team|Greece]].\n\n==Career statistics==\n\n===International===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|colspan=\"3\"|[[Albania national football team|Albania national team]]\n|-\n!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|1998